race.comment: JOHN DORY (1) was smashed in betting from 2.7 into 1.85 on debut but couldn't close quickly enough and found one better over 1300m at Newcastle. Ideally placed out to this trip and that provincial form should hold in this line-up. Stablemate FLAXLANDS (6) was also backed from black to red odds but tasted defeat last start, closing strongly to get up for third last Saturday over 1400m at Hawkesbury. Didn't enjoy the best of luck that day and should have settled closer. Went close in town two back and is a serious threat on the quick back-up. MATIAS (3) made strong late inroads to get up for second when resuming over 1400m at Rosehill recently. Lightly raced three-year-old who is a winning hope with natural improvement to come. SALOON PASSAGE (7) has found the line with purpose in both runs to date in shorter races. This looks to set up nicely. YATTAZOU (8) finished less than a length behind MATIAS when they clashed recently. Progressing well and should be thereabouts.
